Description: Just about to go out for birthday party.  Felt quite tired but was really looking forward to it.  There had just been a big thunderstorm
In Bury about to have dinner, just had a G&T.  Felt a little hungry.

Happened around lunchtime, having bruschetta.
Had stayed in and watched World Cup football previous night.

Flying from Mauritius to Jo'berg.  
Migraine wasn't too bad, felt better in evening.

Started in night, woke 6:30am with numb arm.
Been to see a band the previous day, we were out all day, a few pints of cider and some portion of fish and chips for dinner.

Been in Doncaster the weekend before drove back Sunday afternoon.
Walked to work due to tube strike, had breakfast @9:15.
Started at around 11am, got better by evening.
Was about to go to the cinema.  Started feeling bad after we'd just finished dinner.  Felt better by the next morning.
Just finished Christmas in London back in Kent about to head up to Northampton.  Had eaten and drank lots over past couple of days, also slept well.
Friday night at home, we were due to head off to New Zealand the next day.  Late-ish in the evening, 9:30.  Was quite tired, been out night before.

Woke up just after 9am, went to start watching Grand Prix, migraine started.
Had scallops and bacon and half a bottle of wine the night before.
In Marrakesh about to travel to Essaouira, didn't sleep well during the night, woke up with numb hand, didn't last too long.

Just got back from Morocco, at home in the morning just getting ready to walk into Soho for lunch.
Not been eating or drinking much due to upset stomach from holiday.
Lasted around 24 hours, felt groggy for a day after that.

Woke up at 6:30am and it had started.
Hadn't slept well previous two nights, had salad for previous two nights.
Still felt groggy the day after.
Got back from Germany the night before.  Woke up at 6am, left hand and face felt numb, took tablets, slept till 11am, didn't feel too bad for rest of day.  Went to work the next day, slightly groggy.

Started about 6am Sunday morning.  Had salmon en-crote and Champagne the night before.  Had just moved house.
Didn't take Zomig and had Neurofen at 10am once woke up, didn't feel too bad for rest of day.

Started around 7:30pm once I'd got home from work.  Had been running at lunch, jacket potato with cheese and tuna for lunch.
Had dinner before it go too bad at 8pm, then slept for 1:30 hours got up for a bit and went to bed.
Took the next day off work, didn't feel great in the morning and still felt groggy the day after.  Felt better on the Thursday.

Just before dinner, 8:30ish.  Been swimming (cold pool) then got ready for dinner in warm room, a bit hungry but didn't snack because didn't want to spoil dinner.   
Ordered aperitif and had a mouthful of Bombay mix and it started.

Had been out the previous night - didn't eat much, just a few crisps and Cornish pasty.  Got on bus in to work, felt hungry, made it to Piccadilly Circus when it started.
Turned round and headed home, felt rough all day, back to work the next day.

Woke up, got in shower and it started.  Not too bad, felt better by evening.
Previous lunch, had very hot quesadilla, too many chillies.  For dinner the night before had pizza with courgette and chorizo.  Had some dark chocolate before bed.

Had just got over previous days migraine, just about to have lunch at 2pm and it started very quickly.  Felt really bad till the next day and still felt groggy on Monday.
Had pizza with courgette and chorizo the night before and some dark chocolate.

Monday morning, travelling to work, got to Charing Cross, it started. Felt quite rough, feeling better by evening.
Had Sunday lunch (beef) in Camden at around 2pm, had some Quoin and courgette for supper. Had some dark chocolate before bed.

On train home, slight delay with train, sat in seat with sun in eyes, started half way through.  Went to Pret for lunch, had cheese baguette and banana later. Had chicken soup the night before.
When to bed once got home, got up around 9.  Slept well from 11, felt fine the next day, went to work and for a run.

Started 8am Sunday morning, had really bad headache.  Had been for a BBQ at Nat's the night before, had loads of meat and 4 beers.  Didn't have a proper dinner, just cereal and snacks.  Didn't drink much water during the BBQ.
Had been out on Friday and had beer and a burger at the Anchor.

Had Jubilee BBQ day before.  Felt rough all day, hangover-like. Delicate stomach, headache-y.  Had just had bowl of muesli then was going to bed and migraine started.  BIG block of vision, most top-right, instantly disappeared.  Went straight to bed, slept ok. Took day off work felt a bit rough and then still rough the day after (delicate stomach etc).
Woke up at 4am Sunday morning at Glastonbury. Had pills left ok by breakfast.  Had been feeling rough previous couple of days, felt much better after the migraine.
Had been in Hull, watched Wimbledon final.  Got back home, took rubbish out did a few chores then migraine started.  Felt rough for a few days.
Started 5:30 in the morning, had to take the day off.  Had lingering headache for a few days after.
About 11:30am at work, got migraine, went home.  Back at work on Tuesday.
Started 5pm at work, what feeling fine, been to gym etc.  Had heated discussion then migraine started 10 mins later.  Felt rough until Sunday.
Had been in Southampton for the weekend had stew for dinner on Sunday. Woke up Monday morning and migraine started, felt rough until the following evening.

Had migraine during the night, woke up briefly ~2:30am thought my eyes were going funny, went back to sleep.  Woke up before alarm, felt a bit rough, had a shower didn't feel too bad so went to work. Was ok at work, felt better after more drugs for lunch.
Was ok the next day.
Woke up felt fine.  Just getting in to Victoria, migraine started, got train straight back home.  Went to bed till lunch time, had more drugs feeling a bit better.
Woke up, had shower, migraine started.  Felt rough most of day.  Had noodle, squash and tomato curry soup for dinner.
It happened during the night, went to work the next day.
During annual leave. had a migraine one evening.
About an hour after having pizza it started.  After a long week.
Started Saturday morning after having pizza the night before.
Very tired at work, started on way home.  Had tuna melt for lunch.
Had previous day off work.  Started in early hours of morning, felt rough during day.
Had been off with migraine during day, starting to feel better then got another one in the evening. Had pack of ham and cheese sandwich.

Had been off previous Friday with a cold. Felt rough and had rash over the weekend.  Migraine started early in morning on Monday, didn't really do anything about it until getting up for work and felt very rough.  Felt terrible for next few days, headache finally cleared on Thursday (had Monday and Tuesday off).
Started at 8pm went straight to bed and didn't feel too bad the next bad, went to work.  Had pasta dinner, didn't eat that much the day before.
Had got out of hospital with Jake the previous day, just unwinding and having some dinner when it started.
Just had late afternoon snack, had finished work (from home) for the week and it started
Started middle of the night, got numb hand, still went to work
Started while getting ready for work, took day off, holiday the next day.
Was over in Bath, just gone out to help move an Aston. Stayed out through arura, had pills when got home. Drove down to Devon at 4pm.
Out shopping in Rock had just had a pasty
On holiday in Sommerset, started while asleep didn't really notice, got up in night and felt rough. Made it out to Eden project in afternoon.
Started during the night, around 2am.  Took pills but made it to work, felt rough most of days.
Started during the night, around 4am.  Took pills but made it to work, felt rough most of days.
Started at midday, had to go home.  Felt rough for a few days after.
Had been stick to vomiting and diarrhea.  I'd not eaten for two days, just have a small fish and potato supper and got migraine.
Was getting better from being sick, had been up with Jake from 6:30 then around 9:30 got migraine.
16:10 at work and started getting migraine, went home slept it off. Was back at work the next day.
Woke up 6am had bad headache, missed all of numbness and aurora.  Only took nurofen since missed the start.  Felt rough all day, felt better by the next day.

Got up around 6:30 with Jake, previous few nights she had been up so was quite tired.
Got him fed and dressed, sat down in front of TV (Postman Pat) and it started.  Took day of work, slept during the morning.  Still felt quite rough the next day.
Had stir-fry the night before (big portion, plum sauce).

Met Jim for a drink in Bottles, migraine started within 10 mins of getting there.  Was very hot that week.
Went to bed, slept, when to work the next day.

Was just about to go to bed, went downstairs to watch the 100m final and it started.
Slept, took pills in the night (Jake was up) went to work the next day.
Another evening one.  Had just finished dinner and it started.  Went to work the next day.
Sat in bed reading my book and it started.  Hadn't done much in the evening, had couscous with chicken for tea.  Had been to gym.
I'd just put Jake to bed, came downstairs and it started.  Had pasta for lunch not been to the gym.
Had had a late night before, out for dinner with Jerry.  Just getting up and having breakfast.  Felt quite rough for the rest of the day.
Been working late a few nights.  We were just about to have dinner when it started.  Quickly eat dinner and went to bed.  Felt a bit rough the next day, went to work.
Got up early to go swimming and it started.  Went back to bed and felt better by the afternoon.
Had had a migraine the previous day.  Had been to work and was just relaxing in the evening when it started again.  Went to bed and slept it off.
Was at work about to go out for lunch when it started, went home and slept it off.
Another evening one.  Had just finished dinner and was clearing up when it started.  Took drugs and went to bed, felt better by the morning.
Had just sat down to watch TV after having a steak dinner.  Had been working quite hard the last few days, it had been really cold.  Took the usual drugs and slept it off.  Went to work the next day.
